{"name": "shellinspector", "metadata": {"name": "shellinspector", "version": "0.16.0", "classifiers": ["Development Status :: 4 - Beta", "Programming Language :: Python", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3.10", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3.11", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3.12", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3.9", "Programming Language :: Python :: Implementation :: CPython", "Programming Language :: Python :: Implementation :: PyPy"], "home_page": null, "license": "MIT License", "documentation_url": "https://github.com/uberspace/shellinspector#readme", "dependencies": ["pexpect", "pyyaml", "termcolor"], "summary": null, "upload_time": 1734035391}, "documentation": ["# Shell Inspector \ud83d\udd75\ufe0f\u200d\ufe0f\n\nOpen a shell session locally or via SSH, execute commands, and test what comes\nback.\n\n[![asciicast](https://asciinema.org/a/IfzFtiTPjabw4etcMJmpcuH8f.svg)](https://asciinema.org/a/IfzFtiTPjabw4etcMJmpcuH8f)\n\nFirst, prepare a spec file, e.g. `readme.ispec`:\n\n```\n[@local]$~ ping -c1 google.com\n1 packets transmitted\n[@local]$ whoami\nshellinspector\n```\n\nThen, run it:\n\n```\n$ python -m shellinspector readme.ispec\nrunning readme.console\nPASS [@local]$~ ping -c1 google.com\nFAIL [@local]$ whoami\nexpected:\n    shellinspector\nactual:\n    luto\n```\n\nFor more details have a look at [`docs/syntax.md`](docs/syntax.md).\n"], "modules": [{"name": "shellinspector", "documentation": [], "functions": [], "variables": [], "classes": [], "exports": []}, {"name": "shellinspector.reporter", "documentation": [], "functions": [], "variables": [{"name": "shellinspector.reporter.LOGGER", "type": null, "documentation": []}], "classes": [{"name": "shellinspector.reporter.ConsoleReporter", "bases": [], "methods": [{"name": "shellinspector.reporter.ConsoleReporter.__init__", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "shellinspector.reporter.Console