= \"a\"\n\nIf cmd.host is \"local\", this opens a shell session as the current user\non the current machine. Username and port are ignored. If server is\nremote, this uses the ssh(1) command to establish a connection to the\nserver given in __init__.\n\nIt also makes sure that the environment is as clean as possible, so you\ncan use environment variables freely.\n\nThe yielded session object is a `pexpect.pxssh.pxssh`:\nhttps://pexpect.readthedocs.io/en/stable/api/pxssh.html#pxssh-class"]}, {"name": "shellinspector.runner.ShellRunner.add_reporter", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "reporter", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "shellinspector.runner.ShellRunner.report", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "event", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "cmd", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "kwargs", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "shellinspector.runner.ShellRunner._check_result", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "cmd", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "command_output", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "returncode", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "shellinspector.runner.ShellRunner._run_command", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "session", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "cmd", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "shellinspector.runner.ShellRunner.run", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "specfile", "type": {"name": "Specfile", "xref": {"fqname": "shellinspector.parser.Specfile", "project": null}, "params": null}, "default": null}, {"name": "outer_used_session